reviews.text:
서해의 수군이 활동하는 모든 곳을 관찰 할 수 있는 천혜의 요새이다. 고구려의 비사성이 있는곳으로 고구려 성에서만 볼수 있는 쐐기돌로 이루어진 성을 확인할 수 있다.
고구려의 천리장성이 시작되는 곳이다.
Are you going to extend the Great Wall beyond Korea to the world?

Are you going to extend the Great Wall beyond the Earth to the Moon?

Recently, VANK has analyzed 40 world history textbooks published by major publishers such as Dorling Kindersley(DK), Glencoe, Times, National Geographic, McDougal Littell, Oxford, Pearson Longman, and Apprentice Hall.

The result came out as only 4 books accurately depicted the eastern end of the Great Wall as Shanhaiguan in Hebei Province, near Beijing on the map. However, 7 books depicted the Great Wall as far as North Pyeongan Province and South Pyeongan Province, and 29 volumes depicted the Great Wall as far as Sinuiju and the Amnok River(Yalu River).

Today, 15 years after the Northeast Project (2002-2007), China has removed the traces of Goguryeo Bakjak Fortress near Amnok River from the world history textbooks published by famous publishers around the world, and had built Hushan Fortress on the zone, stubbornly insisting that the fortress belongs to the Great Wall.

What is more serious is that the Great Wall of China is a representative cultural heritage of China that is essentially introduced in famous world history textbooks.

In these world history textbooks, stories about the Great Wall and Emperor Qin Shi Huang are all introduced, but China is secretly stealing the history of Goguryeo and Balhae of Korea using the Great Wall, which is their representative cultural heritage.

If we cannot stop the Chinese government from extorting the history of Goguryeo and Balhae through the Great Wall, in the near future, teenagers worldwide will naturally perceive the history of Goguryeo and Balhae as Chinese history.

American World History textbooks, in particular, are studied by American junior high students. and the distorted perception of history acquired in junior high can have a major impact on them as they become adults.

American textbooks are revised every six years, and California textbooks in particular were revised in 2016 and will be done again in 2022. Accordingly, VANK will inform publishers of the distorted history of the Great Wall not only for California, but throughout the United States, and work on revisions.

Therefore, VANK intends to expand Chinas distortion of the Great Wall not only as a problem of Korea and China, but also to China and other countries around the world.
It's a mystery, it's not a great castle

reviews.text:
The Port Arthur Fortress site is the site of a permanent fortress from the modern war known as the Russo-Japanese War, and the North Fort of East Giguanshan is its most prominent presence.
It is said that many sacrifices were made due to its complex structure and countless crenelations.
Some are questioning the qualifications of Army General Maresuke Nogi, who was the commander of the Third Army, but at that time there was no established method for conquering such a permanent fortress, so trial and error would have been inevitable.
In the end, the Third Army succeeds in digging a tunnel and blowing up the redoubt from underground, but I am deeply moved by the huge scale of the operation, in which they had to dig hundreds of meters by hand to cause a huge explosion.

This is the ruins of a fortified battlefield where many soldiers died during the Russo-Japanese War.
It is quite far from the city center.
It is unclear whether you can go there by city bus.
Since I was traveling alone, I showed the taxi driver at the bus terminal in Port Arthur my destination and was given a round trip ride.

One of the fiercest battles of the Russo-Japanese War. You can see the remains of the bombing and destruction of the walls of the Russian military's sturdy pillboxes, as well as the marks of cannonballs and guns. It was quite a sight to see. Nowadays, it seems to be a tourist attraction for Chinese tourists.
(There is a sightseeing tour in Dalian that includes 203 Highlands/Shishying, which I took advantage of)

reviews.text:
The Dalian Donggang Musical Fountain is a popular attraction known for its captivating performances. The fountain operates daily from 7:30 PM to 9:00 PM, providing a stunning display of lights and music that draws both locals and tourists. Located by the seaside, it offers amazing views of the surrounding skyscrapers and a well-organized promenade with numerous attractions.
The area is well-equipped with few large parking, vendors, rental options for electric cars and bikes,  boats  and a funfair. The public toilet located near  marine .There are also plenty of restaurants, making it a perfect spot for a day out. Signage is available in both Chinese and English, ensuring ease of navigation for all visitors. The site is part of a larger tourist area in Dalian, which includes several hotels  well known for high standard of  service  and offering top-tier accommodations nearby.
The fountain ends a little after 7 o'clock.  The light show on the facades of the four buildings after the fountain is much better than the fountain.  Be sure to check it out.

Interesting large open air bird park. Several hours will fly by unnoticed (at the same time you will listen to the peacocks singing!! :-)). A very decent and picturesque area between the mountains is covered with a large mesh tent. Slopes, trees, bushes, a pond with a small cascade, serpentine paths. Various ducks, geese, swans, peacocks, cranes, chickens and other birds. I saw an albino peacock (all white), black swans and many other interesting birds. I fed the birds with grains of boiled corn (bought at the entrance) by hand. Most likely you can’t feed birds, but I don’t understand hieroglyphs, but hand-feeding peacocks is fun! )) Entrance both from the street and by cable car from the oceanarium. There are parrot shows inside several times a day - quite a decent show. If you want a parrot to fly up to you, prepare large paper bills in advance (they won’t fly after small ones).
Very interesting place to watch birds up close and feed them. Children's favorite.

reviews.text: Interesting modern building that contains a history of Dalian on 2F.  Currently there is a great photography exhibition.  Could do with a cafe in a building this size

It's free and you can enter if you have a passport etc. There are many items from countries such as China, Russia, and Japan. There were important documents that revealed the sad events of the Sino-Japanese War.

A beautiful new museum. Located near Xinghai Square, it exhibits mainly the modern history of Dalian. Of course, it's all in Chinese, so you can admire the photos and exhibits, but you can get a sense of the relationship between Japan and the founding of Manchukuo just by looking at the atmosphere. Since I went on a holiday, there were a lot of families with children, and as you might expect from coming to a museum with children, many of them looked like intellectuals and were intelligent. This modern history seems to be a permanent exhibit, but as a Japanese person, I felt a little overwhelmed by the depictions of Japanese people doing cruel things to Chinese people. However, since it is a city with a large number of Japanese people, I don't think the local people have any bad feelings towards Japanese people as it is an exhibition of past history. I think the people who read this review are probably Japanese people who have a connection to Dalian, so if you have time, please go there. By the way, there is no admission fee required. (lol)

The history of modern Dalian and Port Arthur is on display. Learn about the influence of Russia and Japan. There is also an exhibition about the sad history of the Great War, and we think about the importance of peace.

reviews.text: Horrible place! The purpose of this aquarium is 100% profit and 0% scientifical nor educational. Animals are kept in horrible conditions. In the big tank with the tunnel I saw 3 turtles that were obviously dead (i am assuming because they were stuck in some corner, without moving, with white eyes and pale skin colour). These are protected animals threatened from extinction!!! Don't go there! There are plenty of other aquariums that have an educational/scientifical mission and are very entertaining to visit. This place has to be shut down!

How could you let a gorgeous seal die in your tank? If you’re going to enslave such a gorgeous creature you could at least make sure it’s concrete “home” is safe. It never should have been held captive in the first place. This facility is a tragedy. Shame on you.

The animals here live very tragic lives. :'(

I was unknowingly brought here on a group tour, and it was so horrible, I ran out in tears. Do not support this business, there are many other wonderful places to visit in the area that aren't totally cruel.

data.formatted_address: 3393+J8G, Hai Bin Dong Lu, Jin Zhou Qu, Da Lian Shi, Liao Ning Sheng, China, 116650
data.name: Dalian Coastal National Geopark

reviews.text:
A national park that makes a great hike for hikers as well as geology lovers. Many rocks with different shapes and formations whose geological history is usually well explained on small boards erected besides them. View of the sea is breathtaking, and the sea water is clear. Many locations for a great portrait photo with your favourite poses. The place would surely be flooded with newly-married couples coming for wedding photos if it weren't a ticketed national park so far from downtown. No complaints about the burning sun though, although it made us sweat a lot.

(Photos taken on September 8, 2020.)
Such a nice place for a good view of sea and mountain.
Awesome Geology
Good
The natural rocks form various shapes along the coast. Walking on the trail, in addition to the sea view, you can also touch the wonders of nature.

I bought a round trip to Lushun at the train station. It cost 30 yuan and I thought it was a reasonable price. The ticket description only includes transportation and a tour guide, but does not include admission fees. As a result, it changed to a group tour after driving. The tour guide also started to recommend a package ticket containing 3 points for 360 yuan. If you did not join, you would have to wait at each location for the group members who had purchased the package ticket. After bargaining, I bought a package for 290 yuan. Tickets include the naval base, zoo and boat ride to feed seagulls. I feel like I'm being deceived.
This scenic spot alone is only worth one star, but you can rent a boat and go to the sea to see the Tiger Tail at close range when the Imperial Army blocked the battle at Lushunkou.

data.formatted_address: China, Liao Ning Sheng, Da Lian Shi, Lv Shun Kou Qu, Ji Guan Shan Lu, 长江路1号 邮政编码: 116041
data.name: Dongjiguanshan Scenic Area （South Gate）

reviews.text: The south gate of East Jiguan Mountain Scenic Area is near the North Fortress. East Jiguan Mountain was the battlefield of the final fierce battle of the Russo-Japanese War. The Japanese army blew open the North Fortress and captured Dongji Mountain. Soon Russia declared defeat. The bombed-out entrances, fortress tunnels, and memorial towers used by the Japanese army to declare their victory were now destroyed, with only tourists paying their respects. There is an exhibition hall in the North Fort Scenic Area. There is a silhouette similar to a female head in the corridor of the fortress, named Margaery. One attraction. . You can get off the bus at Wujianfang Station and look for the large East Jiguan Mountain Scenic Area sign on the highway. Follow the directions. In addition to the North Fortress, the scenic spots also include Wangtai Fort and Erlongshan Fortress. The scenic spot has been open to the public free of charge since May 2017. The Wangtai Fort and Erlongshan Fortress are located to the west. Erlongshan Fortress is now a field training camp with large dogs. It takes about 20 minutes to walk from the North Fort to the Watchtower Fort. Going down the hill to the southwest from the fort, you can reach the Japanese-Russian Prison Site Museum, which is about an hour's walk away. Driving tour is more convenient.
This is the site of the Russo-Japanese War.

reviews.text: The hotel is located a little far from the center of Dalian, but this is difficult to consider as a minus. Within walking distance there is a 2-storey supermarket and a bus stop. 5 minutes by bus to a large supermarket with a food area. The hotel has a mini park opposite, table tennis and billiards, and in the evenings there is a restaurant with fresh seafood and reasonable prices. The rooms are a little outdated, but comfortable and spacious, the breakfasts are delicious and varied. I recommend.
The hotel facilities are a bit old but functional. To its credit it was very clean. In addition, the hotel is very quiet, has a good environment and ample parking spaces.
